    "abstract": "<jats:title>Abstract</jats:title>\n                <jats:p>Current RNA vaccines against SARS-CoV-2 are limited by instability of both the RNA and the lipid nanoparticle delivery system, requiring storage at \u221220\u00b0C or \u221270\u00b0C and compromising universally accessible vaccine distribution. This study demonstrates the thermostability and adaptability of a nanostructured lipid carrier (NLC) RNA vaccine delivery system for use in pandemic preparedness and pandemic response. Liquid NLC is stable at refrigerated temperatures for \u2265 1 year, enabling stockpiling and rapid deployment by point-of-care mixing with any vaccine RNA. Alternatively, NLC complexed with RNA may be readily lyophilized and stored at room temperature for \u2265 8 months or refrigerated temperature for \u2265 21 months. This thermostable RNA vaccine platform could significantly improve distribution of current and future pandemic response vaccines, particularly in low-resource settings.</jats:p>\n                <jats:sec>\n                  <jats:title>One Sentence Summary</jats:title>\n                  <jats:p>An RNA vaccine delivery system stable at room temperature for 8+ months and refrigerated for 21+ months.</jats:p>\n                </jats:sec>",
